        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-03-04 13:47:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> (3 comments)\n > \n > Jorge, I am not sure that these messages will come under drools\n > session or not. Anyways we can achieve serialization using\n > Coder/Decoder work that Jim is doing (using gson).\n > @Jim, is that correct?\n\nSession persistence is all done via the Serialization interface and we have no control over it, as it's hidden within drools.  The question is: will this ever have to be persisted by the drools engine?  I kind of doubt it, but not sure.  If it is persisted, then yes, it must implement the Serialization interface.",
